name: CoreAPI Connectivity_Authentication
description: API to access proxy authentication for APIs, OData and remote systems.
about:
Description

The CoreAPI Connectivity_Authentication API enables to access the API authentications that are defined in the Proxy Authentication tool.

With this API, you can list all existing proxy authentication within the system and fetch all information regarding a specific proxy authentication.

Prerequisites: In order for the API to work, you will have to change the endpoint in the General tab.

Operations  performed

Important note: Please review the definitions and the request/response bodies for each operation. In certain definitions, you will a description next each field. If not, view the example data in the selected operation. 

The /Get operation returns a JSON structure that varies depending on the proxy authentication type. Please refer to the five different response bodies below in the /Get operation section.


/List

Get the list of available proxy authentications. Within each object in the returned array, the UUID of each item is placed. This is the same value that /Get operation requires.

Body
Definition
Request
None
Response
List


/Get

Retrieve the proxy authentication details corresponding to the UUID. The default response structure corresponds to a basic proxy authentication.

Body
Definition
Request
ID
Response
Get


Below, you will find the response structures for the remaining proxy authentication types.
